title <size:18>Elevator System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Person on Floor 3 presses UP. Scheduler picks nearest elevator. Elevator moves to Floor 3, opens door, person presses Floor 7 inside."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: BUILDING + FLOORS
' ====================================================================
class Building {
    - floors : vector<Floor*>
    --
    + Building(totalFloors, dispatcher)
    + ~Building()
    + getFloor(floor) : Floor*
}

class Floor {
    - floorNumber : int
    - upButton : ExternalButton
    - downButton : ExternalButton
    --
    + Floor(floorNumber, dispatcher)
    + pressUpButton() : void
    + pressDownButton() : void
}

note top of Building #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "A Building has N Floors. Each Floor has
    two **ExternalButtons**: UP and DOWN.
    Person on Floor 3 presses UP button.
    That triggers the external request flow."
    **Composition: Building -> Floors -> Buttons**
end note

Building *-- Floor : has floors >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: EXTERNAL REQUEST FLOW
' ====================================================================
class ExternalButton {
    - dispatcher : ExternalDispatcher*
    --
    + ExternalButton(dispatcher)
    + pressButton(floor, direction) : void
}

class ExternalDispatcher <<Facade>> {
    + scheduler : ElevatorScheduler*
    --
    + ExternalDispatcher(scheduler)
    + submitExternalRequest(floor, direction) : void
}

note top of ExternalDispatcher #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - External request flow.**
    "Person presses UP on Floor 3.
    ExternalButton delegates to
    **ExternalDispatcher** (Facade).
    Dispatcher delegates to ElevatorScheduler
    to pick the best elevator."

    "Flow: Button -> Dispatcher -> Scheduler
    -> Strategy -> Controller -> ElevatorCar"
end note

Floor *-- ExternalButton : has up/down buttons >
ExternalButton --> ExternalDispatcher : delegates >
ExternalDispatcher --> ElevatorScheduler : schedules via >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: ELEVATOR SELECTION — Strategy Pattern (KEY)
' ====================================================================
class ElevatorScheduler {
    - controllers : vector<ElevatorController*>
    - strategy : ElevatorSelectionStrategy*
    --
    + ElevatorScheduler(controllers, strategy)
    + setStrategy(strategy) : void
    + assignElevator(floor, direction) : ElevatorController*
}

abstract class ElevatorSelectionStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    --
    + {abstract} selectElevator(controllers, requestFloor, direction) : ElevatorController*
}

class NearestElevatorStrategy {
    --
    + selectElevator(controllers, requestFloor, direction) : ElevatorController*
}

class LeastBusyStrategy {
    --
    + selectElevator(controllers, requestFloor, direction) : ElevatorController*
}

note top of ElevatorSelectionStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - Which elevator? (KEY STEP)**
    "Multiple elevators. Which one should serve
    Floor 3 UP? **Strategy Pattern:**"

    "**NearestElevatorStrategy** (multi-level logic):
    1. Prefer elevator going same direction AND
       hasn't passed the floor (e.g., Elev 1 at
       Floor 1 going UP = distance 2).
    2. Fallback: pick idle elevator.
    3. Final fallback: pick first available."

    "**LeastBusyStrategy**:
    Total load = upQueue.size + downQueue.size.
    Pick elevator with minimum load."

    "setStrategy() swaps at runtime.
    Add ZoneBasedStrategy? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

ElevatorSelectionStrategy <|-- NearestElevatorStrategy
ElevatorSelectionStrategy <|-- LeastBusyStrategy
ElevatorScheduler --> ElevatorSelectionStrategy : delegates >
ElevatorScheduler o--> ElevatorController : manages >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: ELEVATOR CONTROLLER — Thread-Safe Queues (KEY)
' ====================================================================
class ElevatorController {
    - upMinPQ : priority_queue<int, greater>
    - downMaxPQ : priority_queue<int>
    - elevatorCar : ElevatorCar*
    - mtx : mutex
    - cv : condition_variable
    --
    + ElevatorController(elevatorCar)
    + submitRequest(destinationFloor) : void
    + getUpQueueSize() : int
    + getDownQueueSize() : int
    + run() : void
    + controlElevator() : void
    - enqueueRequest(destinationFloor) : void
}

note top of ElevatorController #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - The brain. (KEY STEP)**
    "Each elevator has its own ElevatorController
    running in a **separate thread**."

    "**Two priority queues** (SCAN algorithm):
    **upMinPQ** (min-heap): floors to visit going UP.
       [3, 5, 7] -> visit 3 first, then 5, then 7.
    **downMaxPQ** (max-heap): floors going DOWN.
       [8, 5, 2] -> visit 8 first, then 5, then 2."

    "**Thread-safe** with mutex + condition_variable:
    submitRequest() locks, enqueues, notifies CV.
    controlElevator() waits on CV when idle,
    wakes up when request arrives."

    "This is the SCAN/Elevator Algorithm."
    **Patterns: Producer-Consumer, SCAN Algorithm**
end note

ElevatorController --> ElevatorCar : controls >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: ELEVATOR CAR + DOOR
' ====================================================================
class ElevatorCar {
    - id : int
    - currentFloor : int
    - nextFloorStoppage : int
    - movingDirection : ElevatorDirection
    - door : Door
    --
    + ElevatorCar(id)
    + showDisplay() : void
    + moveElevator(destinationFloor) : void
    + setCurrentFloor(floor) : void
}

class Door {
    - doorState : DoorState
    --
    + Door()
    + openDoor(id) : void
    + closeDoor(id) : void
}

enum ElevatorDirection {
    UP
    DOWN
    IDLE
}

enum DoorState {
    DOOR_OPEN
    DOOR_CLOSED
}

note top of ElevatorCar #C8E6C9
    **STEP 5 - The physical elevator.**
    "**ElevatorCar** has: id, currentFloor,
    direction (UP/DOWN/IDLE), and a Door."

    "**moveElevator(destinationFloor)**:
    1. Close door
    2. Update direction (UP or DOWN)
    3. Move floor by floor to destination
    4. Arrive: update currentFloor
    5. Open door (passengers enter/exit)
    6. Close door"

    "**Door** has simple state: OPEN/CLOSED.
    openDoor() and closeDoor() with logging."
end note

ElevatorCar *-- Door : has >
ElevatorCar --> ElevatorDirection


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: INTERNAL REQUEST FLOW — Singleton
' ====================================================================
class InternalButton {
    - controller : ElevatorController*
    --
    + InternalButton(controller)
    + pressButton(destinationFloor) : void
}

class InternalDispatcher <<Singleton>> {
    - InternalDispatcher()
    --
    + {static} getInstance() : InternalDispatcher&
    + submitInternalRequest(floor, controller) : void
}

note top of InternalDispatcher #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Inside the elevator.**
    "Person enters elevator, presses Floor 7.
    **InternalButton** delegates to
    **InternalDispatcher** (Singleton) which
    submits request directly to that
    elevator's controller."

    "**Singleton** because all internal buttons
    across all elevators use the same dispatcher.
    Single point of contact for internal requests."

    "Internal vs External:
    External: 'I need AN elevator at Floor 3'
    Internal: 'THIS elevator, go to Floor 7'"
    **Pattern: Singleton | SRP**
end note

InternalButton --> InternalDispatcher : delegates >
InternalDispatcher --> ElevatorController : submits to >


' ====================================================================
'  CONNECTIONS
' ====================================================================
Building --> ExternalDispatcher : wired to >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Person on Floor 3 presses UP -> ExternalButton ->
    ExternalDispatcher -> ElevatorScheduler uses **Strategy** (Nearest
    or LeastBusy) to pick best elevator -> ElevatorController receives
    request in thread-safe priority queue -> Controller's thread wakes
    up, processes SCAN algorithm (min-heap UP, max-heap DOWN) ->
    ElevatorCar moves to Floor 3, opens Door -> Person enters, presses
    Floor 7 via InternalButton -> **Singleton** InternalDispatcher ->
    same Controller enqueues Floor 7 -> car moves to Floor 7."

    "Key patterns: **Strategy** (elevator selection), **Singleton**
    (InternalDispatcher), **Facade** (ExternalDispatcher),
    **Composition** (Building->Floor->Button), **SCAN Algorithm**
    (dual priority queues), **Thread-per-Elevator** (mutex + CV)."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= Key Point |
    | 1 | Building has Floors, each Floor has UP/DOWN ExternalButtons | Composition | Physical hierarchy |
    | 2 | Button -> ExternalDispatcher -> ElevatorScheduler | Facade | External request flow |
    | 3 | Scheduler picks best elevator: Nearest or LeastBusy | Strategy | Pluggable selection algorithm |
    | 4 | Controller enqueues in min-heap (UP) / max-heap (DOWN) | SCAN Algorithm | Thread-safe with mutex + CV |
    | 5 | ElevatorCar moves floor-by-floor, opens/closes Door | Composition | Physical elevator + door |
    | 6 | Inside elevator: InternalButton -> Singleton Dispatcher -> Controller | Singleton | Internal request flow |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **External Flow** = Steps 1-3 (floor button -> scheduler -> controller) | **Internal Flow** = Step 6 (car button -> dispatcher -> controller) | **Movement** = Steps 4-5 (SCAN + car) |  |
endlegend

@enduml
